CLII. 1. MINERVA TO VENUS.

This, with its pendant, No. 2, forms a pair of poems, in which an epistolary debate between the two rival goddesses, presiding over wisdom and love respectively, is instituted. The whole is a fine tesselation of gems from ancient mythology enriched with ore of more modern fancy,

and the vein recalls the kindred contest in the “ Princess'’ of Tennyson between the Lady Blanche and Lady Psyche.
